    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Available is a museum-grade 2002 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, equipped with individual throttle bodies and a 7,900 RPM redline. This example is mechanically superlative, featuring a documented rear subframe reinforcement and a comprehensive VANOS system overhaul. Power is managed via a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission and a factory M-Variable limited-slip differential. The chassis dynamics are sharpened by fresh OEM bushings and a perfectly calibrated suspension geometry, ensuring zero play in the steering rack. Finished in Laguna Seca Blue, the exterior retains its factory luster with no signs of thermal cycling on the plastic components. This is a turn-key, investment-grade driver for the purist who demands peak atmospheric performance.",
